From: Paul Philippov <paul@themactep.com>
Date: Sat, 31 Aug 2025 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix musl libc poll header warning in hackbench

Replace deprecated <sys/poll.h> with standard <poll.h> to eliminate
musl libc warning about incorrect include path.

musl libc redirects <sys/poll.h> to <poll.h> and issues a warning.
Using the standard <poll.h> header directly eliminates this warning
while maintaining compatibility with both glibc and musl.

Signed-off-by: Paul Philippov <paul@themactep.com>
---
 src/hackbench/hackbench.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/hackbench/hackbench.c b/src/hackbench/hackbench.c
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/src/hackbench/hackbench.c
+++ b/src/hackbench/hackbench.c
@@ -23,7 +23,7 @@
 #include <sys/socket.h>
 #include <sys/wait.h>
 #include <sys/time.h>
-#include <sys/poll.h>
+#include <poll.h>
 #include <limits.h>
 #include <getopt.h>
 #include <signal.h>
